article.story: DALLAS -- — Samuell Williamson's 18 points helped SMU defeat Houston Christian 89-53 on Tuesday night. Williamson added eight rebounds for the Mustangs (8-4). Keon Ambrose-Hylton added 12 points while going 4 of 5 and 4 of 4 from the free-throw line, and he also had three blocks. Zhuric Phelps had 11 points and was 5-of-12 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range). Michael Imariagbe had 12 points and 12 rebounds for the Huskies (2-8) . Marcus Greene also added 12 points and two steals for Houston Christian. Pierce Bazil had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
